      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Ron Sexsmith - With Special Guest: Terra Spencer"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Glasgow Square Theatre in partnership with 'East Coaster Studios' is proud to present a special\nevening with Ron Sexsmith, the three-time Juno Award-winning singer-songwriter whose\ntimeless melodies and heartfelt lyrics have made him a beloved fixture in Canada's music\nlandscape for over three decades.</p>\n\n<p>From humble beginnings in Toronto's club scene to acclaimed albums produced by the likes of\nMitchell Froom and Daniel Lanois, Sexsmith has quietly built a global following and earned\npraise from legends like Elvis Costello, Elton John, and Paul McCartney. His tender,\nintrospective songwriting has not only won the hearts of fans but inspired covers by Rod\nStewart, Emmy Lou Harris, Feist, Stevie Nicks, and more.</p>\n\n<p>Described by Rolling Stone as 'the most fluent balladeer to come along since Tim Hardin or\nHarry Nilsson,' Sexsmith's blend of classic pop, folk, and roots-rock delivers a live\nperformance that is both deeply personal and profoundly moving.\nDon't miss this chance to experience the magic of one of Canada's most revered musical\nstorytellers—live in the intimate setting of the Glasgow Square Theatre in New Glasgow, NS</p>\n\n<p>Nova Scotian, singer-songwriter, Terra Spencer will open the show. </p>\n\n\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>\n\n"
      }
    ],
