    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "SUBHUMAN - Preview"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Award-winning writer, Natalie Meisner, and director, Pamela Halstead return to the Osprey stage with another comedy about serious stuff. SubHuman is a story about the Navy Wrens who 'served in silence' at CFB Shelburne only to be unjustly purged from the service because of their sexual orientation. As a prequel to 'Area 33,' SubHuman once again demonstrates Meisner's unique ability to find the humour, intelligence and heart inside a story where perhaps none of those things should exist. SubHuman begins with a preview on July 8 and runs from July 9-12, including a matinee on Saturday, July 11 and closing with a matinee on July 12.</p>\n\n\n<style>\n    .titleTax {\n       display: none !important;\n   }\n</style>\n\n"
      }
    ],
